What you need to know:

The handshake, and the Building Bridges Initiative, have also made President Kenyatta more assertive at a stage in his final term when he should ordinarily have started to become a “lame duck” as successors queue ahead of 2022.Like Mr Odinga in the disputed 2007 presidential elections, supporters of the DP believe he has the pulse of the nation at the moment and should use the opportunity to craft a winning team.